column1:
With bars as( 
	SELECT bar,MAX(times_a_week) 
	FROM Frequents 
	GROUP BY bar
)
SELECT DISTINCT Frequents.bar, Frequents.drinker
FROM bars 
Join Frequents
on Frequents.times_a_week = bars.max and Frequents.bar = bars.bar;

SELECT f.bar, f.drinker 
FROM Frequents f,  
	(SELECT bar, MAX(times_a_week)
	FROM Frequents
	GROUP BY bar) t
WHERE f.bar = t.bar 
AND f.times_a_week = t.max;

-- For each bar, find the drinker who frequents it the greatest 
-- number of times. Your output should be a list of (bar, drinker) pairs.
-- If multiple drinkers tie for  the most frequent visitor to bar,
-- list them all as separate pairs.

SELECT bar, drinker
FROM frequents 
WHERE (bar, times_a_week) IN 
(
	SELECT bar, MAX(times_a_week)
	FROM frequents
	GROUP BY bar
);

WITH temp1 (bar2, maxTime) AS(
SELECT bar, MAX(times_a_week)
FROM frequents
GROUP BY bar)

SELECT DISTINCT bar, frequents.drinker
FROM frequents, temp1
WHERE times_a_week = maxTime AND bar = bar2;

column1:
SELECT bar, drinker
FROM Frequents
WHERE (drinker, bar, times_a_week) IN 
(SELECT *
FROM Frequents
WHERE (drinker, bar, times_a_week) NOT IN
(SELECT freq1.drinker, freq1.bar, freq1.times_a_week
FROM Frequents freq1, Frequents freq2
WHERE (freq1.bar = freq2.bar) AND (freq1.times_a_week <
freq2.times_a_week)
)
);

column1:
SELECT frequents.bar, frequents.drinker
FROM frequents, (SELECT bar, MAX(times_a_week) AS num
	FROM frequents
	GROUP BY bar) get
WHERE frequents.times_a_week = get.num and frequents.bar = get.bar
ORDER BY frequents.bar;

-- For each bar, find the drinker who frequents it the greatest number of times. Your output should be
-- a list of (bar, drinker) pairs. If multiple drinkers tie for the most frequent visitor to a bar, list them all
-- as separate pairs.

(select distinct bar, drinker from frequents)
except
(select freq1.bar, freq1.drinker
from frequents as freq1
join frequents
on freq1.bar=frequents.bar and freq1.times_a_week<frequents.times_a_week);

SELECT frequents.bar, frequents.drinker 
FROM frequents
EXCEPT 
(SELECT f1.bar, f1.drinker
FROM frequents AS f1, frequents AS f2

select bar, drinker
from Frequents f
where not exists 
(select bar, drinker from Frequents
where times_a_week > f.times_a_week
and bar = f.bar);

column1:
SELECT y.bar, y.drinker
FROM (
	SELECT bar, max(times_a_week) AS mx
	FROM frequents
	GROUP BY bar
)	x JOIN frequents y ON x.bar = y.bar AND x.mx = y.times_a_week
;

column1:
SELECT a.bar, a.drinker
FROM frequents a
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT bar, MAX(times_a_week) times_a_week
    FROM frequents
    GROUP BY bar
) b ON a.bar = b.bar AND a.times_a_week = b.times_a_week;

column1:
select distinct fr1.bar, fr1.drinker
from  frequents fr1
where not exists
(
	select 1
    from  frequents fr2
    where fr1.bar = fr2.bar
    and fr1.times_a_week < fr2.times_a_week
);

SELECT
TimeTable.bar,
drinker
FROM
(SELECT
bar,
MAX(times_a_week) AS MaxTimes
FROM
Frequents
GROUP BY
bar) AS TimeTable
JOIN
Frequents ON TimeTable.MaxTimes = Frequents.times_a_week
WHERE
TimeTable.bar = Frequents.bar
;

column1:
SELECT f1.bar, f1.drinker
FROM Frequents AS f1 JOIN (
    SELECT bar, MAX(times_a_week) AS times_a_week
    FROM Frequents
    GROUP BY bar
) AS f2
ON f1.bar=f2.bar AND f1.times_a_week=f2.times_a_week;

column1:
select distinct f1.bar, f1.drinker
from frequents as f1
full join (
select distinct bar, max(times_a_week)
from frequents
group by bar) as f2
on f1.bar = f2.bar
group by f1.bar, f1.drinker, f2.max
having f1.times_a_week = f2.max;

SELECT FINAL.bar, FINAL.drinker
FROM
(
  SELECT frequents.drinker, frequents.bar, frequents.times_a_week
  FROM frequents
  EXCEPT
  SELECT T.drinker1, T.bar1, T.num1
  FROM
    (
    SELECT f1.drinker AS drinker1, f2.drinker AS drinker2, f1.bar AS bar1, f2.bar AS bar2, f1.times_a_week AS num1, f2.times_a_week AS num2
    FROM frequents AS f1, frequents AS f2
    WHERE f1.times_a_week < f2.times_a_week
    AND f1.bar = f2.bar
    ) T
) FINAL

With t1 as (select bar, max(times_a_week) as max_week
from frequents 
group by bar)

select frequents.bar, frequents.drinker
from frequents join t1 
on frequents.times_a_week = t1.max_week and frequents.bar = t1.bar;

/*g) For each bar, find the drinker who frequents it the greatest number of times. Your output should be
#a list of (bar, drinker) pairs. If multiple drinkers tie for the most frequent visitor to a bar, list them all
#as separate pairs.

#these are the top bars and times a week*/
SELECT top_bars.bar, all_bars.drinker FROM (SELECT f1.bar, f1.times_a_week
	FROM frequents f1 INNER JOIN frequents f2 ON (f1.bar = f2.bar) WHERE (f1.times_a_week >= f2.times_a_week)
EXCEPT
SELECT f1.bar, f1.times_a_week
	FROM frequents f1 INNER JOIN frequents f2 ON (f1.bar = f2.bar) 
	WHERE f1.times_a_week < f2.times_a_week) as top_bars
INNER JOIN frequents all_bars ON (top_bars.bar = all_bars.bar and top_bars.times_a_week=all_bars.times_a_week); /*#connect top bars and times a week with people*/

column1:
SELECT frequents.bar, drinker
FROM frequents, 
	(SELECT bar, MAX(times_a_week)
	FROM frequents
	GROUP BY bar)
	AS maxes
WHERE frequents.bar = maxes.bar
AND frequents.times_a_week = maxes.MAX;

Select bar, drinker
From frequents as f1
Where NOT Exists (Select bar, drinker
					From frequents
					Where bar = f1.bar
					And times_a_week > f1.times_a_week);

column1:
SELECT f.bar, f.drinker
	FROM frequents as f, 
		(SELECT bar, MAX(times_a_week) as times_a_week
		FROM frequents
		GROUP BY bar) as maxF
	WHERE f.bar = maxF.bar
		AND f.times_a_week = maxF.times_a_week;

FROM frequents, (SELECT max(times_a_week) AS freq,bar FROM frequents GROUP BY bar) AS maxview
WHERE (frequents.times_a_week = maxview.freq)
AND (frequents.bar = maxview.bar);

(select bar, drinker FROM frequents)
EXCEPT
(SELECT DISTINCT frequents1.bar as bar1, frequents1.drinker as drinker1
FROM frequents as frequents1, frequents as frequents2
WHERE frequents1.times_a_week < frequents2.times_a_week
AND frequents1.bar = frequents2.bar
AND frequents1.drinker <> frequents2.drinker);

WITH Max_Table(bar, times_a_week) AS
(SELECT bar, MAX(times_a_week) AS times_a_week
FROM Frequents
GROUP BY bar)
SELECT Frequents.bar, Frequents.drinker
FROM Frequents, Max_Table
WHERE Frequents.bar = Max_Table.bar
AND Frequents.times_a_week = Max_Table.times_a_week;

SELECT FINAL.bar, FINAL.drinker
FROM (SELECT frequents.drinker, frequents.bar, frequents.times_a_week
  FROM frequents EXCEPT
  SELECT T.drinker1, T.bar1, T.num1 FROM
    (SELECT f1.drinker AS drinker1, f2.drinker AS drinker2, f1.bar AS bar1, f2.bar AS bar2, f1.times_a_week AS num1, f2.times_a_week AS num2
    FROM frequents AS f1, frequents AS f2
    WHERE f1.times_a_week < f2.times_a_week
    AND f1.bar = f2.bar) T) FINAL;

WITH 
tmp1(drinker1, bar1, times_a_week1) AS
(SELECT * FROM frequents),

tmp2(drinker2, bar2, times_a_week2) AS
(SELECT * FROM frequents),

tmp3(drinker, bar, times_a_week) AS
(SELECT drinker1, bar1, times_a_week1 FROM (tmp1 JOIN tmp2 ON tmp1.times_a_week1<tmp2.times_a_week2 AND tmp1.bar1=tmp2.bar2)),

tmp4(drinker, bar, times_a_week) AS
(SELECT * FROM frequents EXCEPT SELECT * FROM tmp3),

ans(bar, drinker) AS
(
	SELECT bar, drinker FROM tmp4
)

SELECT * FROM ans;

SELECT bar, drinker
FROM frequents
WHERE frequents.times_a_week >= ALL(
	SELECT times_a_week
	FROM frequents as f
	WHERE frequents.drinker != f.drinker AND frequents.bar = f.bar
	);

FROM
Frequents
EXCEPT
(
  SELECT Frequents.bar,Frequents.drinker
  FROM
  Frequents
  JOIN
  Frequents as f1 ON Frequents.bar = f1.Bar
  WHERE
  (Frequents.times_a_week < f1.times_a_week)
);

  Select bar, Max(times_a_week)
  From frequents
  Group By bar);

AND frequents.times_a_week = max_times_a_week.max;

from frequents, (select bar, max(times_a_week) as maxi

/*For each bar, find the drinker who frequents it the greatest number of times. Your output should be
a list of (bar, drinker) pairs. If multiple drinkers tie for the most frequent visitor to a bar, list them all
as separate pairs. */

(SELECT DISTINCT bar, drinker 
FROM frequents)
EXCEPT
(SELECT DISTINCT A.bar, A.drinker
FROM frequents A, frequents B
WHERE A.bar = B.bar
AND A.times_a_week < B.times_a_week);

SELECT maxes.bar, frequents.drinker
FROM frequents, (SELECT bar, MAX(times_a_week)
	FROM frequents
	GROUP BY bar) AS maxes
WHERE frequents.bar=maxes.bar AND maxes.max=frequents.times_a_week;

FROM Frequents)

FROM Frequents AS Frequents2
INNER JOIN Frequents ON Frequents2.times_a_week < Frequents.times_a_week
AND Frequents2.bar = Frequents.bar);

column1:
SELECT bar,drinker FROM frequents 
EXCEPT 
(SELECT f1.bar,f1.drinker 
	FROM frequents AS f1, frequents AS f2 
	WHERE f1.times_a_week < f2.times_a_week AND f1.bar = f2.bar );
